&gt;ThisEscape illustrates an important special case of Escape - when the *this* references escapes during construction. When the inner EvenListener instance is publised ,so is the enclosing ThisEsape instance.But and object is in a predictable ,consistent state only after its constructuor return. so publishing an object from within its constructor can publish an incompletely constructed object.This is true even if the publication is the last statement in the constructor.If the this reference escapes during construction, the object is considered not properly constructed.

